UID:iRoRCVutxBZu97zSMOhHX
SUMMARY:90th Annual Kirkland Awards Luncheon
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260213T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:What makes a community truly exceptional? The people who lead w
	ith heart\, serve with purpose\, and make a lasting impact every single da
	y. Join us for one of the most meaningful events of the year - the 90th An
	nual Kirkland Chamber Award's Luncheon - where we honor the individuals\, 
	businesses\, and organizations whose dedication helps our community thrive
	. Event Details: Date: Friday\, February 13th Time: 11:30 AM - 1:30 PM \\(
	doors open at 11 AM for networking\\) Ticket Cost: $65 members\, $89 non-m
	embers. Lunch is included. This inspiring afternoon brings together leader
	s\, changemakers\, and neighbors to recognize excellence across even signa
	ture awards. Every honoree reflects the spirit of Kirkland: connection\, s
	ervice\, generosity\, and innovation. From visionary business leaders who 
	innovate and raise the bar to dedicated volunteers who never ask for credi
	t\, to passionate artists who bring the city to life\, and generous philan
	thropists\, this is our moment to celebrate them. ﻿﻿Be part of an upliftin
	g afternoon that reminds us what community is all about. This event has be
	en brought to you by: EvergreenHealth\, Gesa Credit Union\, Kirkland Commu
	nity Foundation\, Lee Johnson Auto Group\, Plymouth Housing\, and Port of 
	Seattle\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/90th-annual-kirkland-awar
	ds-luncheon/17976534/2026-02-13T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:E6KkeNS74QBGUcYfRK7EN
SUMMARY:Screen Printing Open Session
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260213T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:You MUST take the SP 101: Intro to Vera's Screen Print Studio c
	lass before you can sign up for an Open Session\\\\\\*\\*\\* Vera’s screen
	 print studio offers four-hour Open Sessions where individuals who have co
	mpleted the introductory class may use our screen print lab to work on the
	ir own projects. Our Open Sessions are looked over by a volunteer moderato
	r\, who can provide you with advice and guidance for anything taught in ou
	r Screen Printing 101 class. We offer three different kinds of tickets at 
	Open Sessions: Vacuum Table for paper and other flat media\, T-shirt Press
	 for shirts\, tote bags and other fabrics\, and Screen prep for just scree
	n preparation. Each ticket is limited to two. If the ticket you are lookin
	g for is sold out\, please add yourself to the waitlist so you can be noti
	fied when a ticket becomes available. For Open Sessions\, Vera provides: -
	 Rentable screens - Emulsion and emulsion remover - Squegees - Basic tools
	 like spatulas\, rulers\, tape\, etc. Participants must provide their own:
	 - Substrate \\(paper\, t-shirts\, etc\\) - Water based ink Vera \\*does n
	ot\\* allow the use of non-water based inks at our studio\, as our studio 
	is not set up to safely process non-water based ink. If you have any quest
	ions\, please email matt@theveraproject.org. \\*\\*FAQ\\*\\* 1. Can Vera p
	rint a transparent stencil for me? Yes — You must send us your stencil at 
	least 24 hours before the start of your session. Your file must be a .PDF\
	, no larger than 12" x 18"\, and ready to print. Vera cannot make any edit
	s to your file. Stencils are $5 each and can be paid via Debit/Credit when
	 you arrive. If you are not interested in getting a stencil printed at Ver
	a\, you can print your own on transparency at a FedEx or similar print ser
	vice location. 2. What if I need direct assistance on my projects? Our mod
	erators are trained to assist with any topics covered in the SP 101 class 
	offered at Vera. While some may be able to give you basic advice on your p
	roject\, they are not expected to ask as a direct instructor. If you have 
	a project where you would like one-on-one guidance\, please reach out to m
	att@theveraproject.org to request private tutoring. 3. I really want to us
	e your studio during an Open Session\, but there are no slots available? O
	ur studio is in high demand\, so we apologize if our Open Session is sold 
	out — We have limited space in the studio and several events every day at 
	Vera\, so it can be difficult for us to find more time for Open Sessions. 
	If you're interested in booking the studio outside of Open Sessions\, plea
	se email matt@theveraproject.org to discuss private rental rates and avail
	ability.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/screen-printing-open-sess
	ion/14809996/2026-02-13T00
LOCATION:Book-It Repertory Theatre\, 305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Y0JSt4lmASSot3eRPzuDG
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260214T080000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nF
	rom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
